{
  "texts": [
    "Region (II) in the same image (b) is the 'valley' where a void exists between the left and right positive phases and where the positive phase is deeper than the corresponding cross-section.",
    "The thresholding methods incorrectly identify part of the areas with bright contrast, especially on the lower side, as the positive phase.",
    "Meanwhile, FCN-8s and U-Net correctly identified these areas as a negative phase, which was not affected by the depth reflection.",
    "Figure 3c is a magnified image of the upper part of Fig. 3a, where the contrast is relatively bright.",
    "Because the voids are sparsely distributed, and the entire image's contrast is bright, the thresholding methods do not segment the relatively shallow part of the voids very well."
  ]
}